<!DOCTYPE html>
{{> header}}

<div class="sixteen columns">
  <h2>Software Installation</h2>

  The following steps should be completed first before installing any other software:

  <ul class="square">
    <li><a href="/ucn/register">Create user accunt</a></li>
    <li><a href="/ucn/admin">Add devices (admin)</a></li>
  </ul>

  Once the account is ready, install platform specific software on each registered device as explained below:

  <h3>Mac (OS X)</h3>

  <ul class="square">
    <li>Install and activate VPN profile.
        <ul class="dot">
            <li>Download <a href="/ucn/downloads/ucnstudy.{{country}}.mobileconfig">VPN configuration profile</a> to the device (right-click and 'Save as ...').</li>
            <li>Double-click the file to install, click twice 'Continue' and ignore username. Requires user to type in his password to complete.</li>
            <li>Open System Preferences -> Network and select 'UCN Study' from the left column. Check 'Show VPN status in menu bar' for quick access to VPN connect/disconnect.</li>
            <li>Click 'Connect' and provide the device specific VPN login (username.devicename) and user password (same for all devices) created above.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>iPhone/iPad (iOS)</h3>

  <ul class="square">
    <li>Install and activate VPN profile.
        <ul class="dot">
            <li>Download <a href="/ucn/downloads/ucnstudy.{{country}}.mobileconfig">VPN configuration profile</a> to the device (right-click and 'Save as ...').</li>
            <li>Double-click the file to install. TODO: test this.</li>
            <li>Click 'Connect' and provide the device specific VPN login (username.devicename) and user password (same for all devices) created above.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Install and configure <a target="_blank" href="http://appstore.com/moves">Moves</a>.
        <ul class="dot">
            <li>Open Moves app and create a new user profile.</li>
            <li>Request Moves authentication at <a href="/ucn/admin">the device admin page</a>.</li>
            <li>In the Moves app, add a new 3rd party application using the authentication code from previous step. TODO: provide details.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Android</h3>

  <ul class="square">
    <li>Configure and activate the VPN (Settings -> Wireless &amp; Networks -> More -> VPN -> Add VPN Profile):
        <ul class="dot">
            <li>Name : UCN Study</li>
            <li>Type : IPSec PSK</li>
            <li>Server Address : {{vpnserver}}</li>
            <li>IPSec pre-shared key : {{vpnkey}}</li>
            <li>Click 'Save' and then the name of the profile to connect.</li>
            <li>Provide the device specific VPN login (username.devicename) and user password (same for all devices) created above.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Install <a target="_blank" href="/ucn/downloads/UCNDataCollector.apk">UCN activity logger</a> and start the app (can run on the background all the time).</li>
    <li>Install and configure <a target="_blank" href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.protogeo.moves">Moves</a>.
        <ul class="dot">
            <li>Open Moves app and create a new user profile.</li>
            <li>Request Moves authentication at <a href="/ucn/admin">the device admin page</a>.</li>
            <li>In the Moves app, add a new 3rd party application using the authentication code from previous step. TODO: provide details.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Windows PC</h3>

  <ul class="square">
    <li><a target="_blank" href="https://openvpn.net/index.php/open-source/downloads.html">OpenVPN</a></li> 
    <li><a target="_blank" href="https://muse.inria.fr/~george/sample.cmd">OpenVPN configuration script</a> (run as administrator!)</li> 
    <li><a target="_blank" href="/ucn/downloads/hostviewinstaller.exe">UCN activity logger</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Linux</h3>

  <ul class="square">
    <li><a href="/ucn/downloads/{{country}}.server.ovpn">VPN tunnel config combined UDP + TCP fallback</a>
  </ul>

</div>

{{> footer}}

</body>
</html>
